com.i2group.apollo.model.security.transport

Class SecurityTag

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.i2group.apollo.model.security.transport.SecurityTag

  • public final class SecurityTag
extends Object
    A named container for SecurityAccessPermissions and SecurityGrantPermissions that can be used to provide security information for an Item.
    Since:
    4.0

      • SecurityTag

        public SecurityTag(String id,
           String displayName,
           Collection<SecurityAccessPermission> accessPermissions,
           Collection<SecurityGrantPermission> grantPermissions)
        Constructs a new SecurityTag, initializing all mandatory fields.
        Parameters:
        id - A String containing the identifier of this SecurityTag. The identifier must be unique across all SecurityTags in all SecurityTagGroups.
        displayName - A String containing a human-readable name for this SecurityTag.
        accessPermissions - The SecurityAccessPermissions that this SecurityTag contains.
        grantPermissions - The SecurityGrantPermissions that this SecurityTag contains.
